{
  "texts": [
    "By the definition of powerset possibilization, h(x)R(AtF) ℘ i h(y) iff h(y) ⊆ R AtF i [h(x)].",
    "Since F satisfies R⇔win, it satisfies R-down.",
    "Thus, as noted after Definition 4.15, the relationR AtF i in AtF is such that for all a, b ∈ AtF, aR AtF i b iff aR F i b.",
    "Thus, h(y) ⊆ R AtF i [h(x)] iff h(y) ⊆ R F i [h(x)].",
    "Putting all of this together with the definition of h, we haveh(x)R (AtF) ℘ i h(y) iff {b ∈ AtF | b ⊑ F y} ⊆ R F i [{a ∈ AtF | a ⊑ F x}], (4.2)so we must show that the right side is equivalent to xR F i y."
  ]
